   {:e #blake3 "b153cd0c720a9547a000fbb7e6ea3e9b42a5a916711361f95808693572cc9a31" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Tests that verify the complete concept lifecycle: observation → concept update → crystallization → evolution. Each test validates an end-to-end property that was previously untestable (dead code). UNIT TESTS in concept.rs: (1) test_concept_member_count_increments — mock store with innate concept, simulate 3 joins, verify member_count goes 0→1→2→3. (2) test_concept_centroid_shifts — after 5 observations in one direction, centroid is closer to observations than to original. (3) test_concept_total_weight_accumulates — total_weight >= member_count after N joins with surprise > 0. (4) test_crystallize_uncategorized — 6 observations (3 similar, 3 unrelated), crystallize_concepts produces 1 concept from the 3 similar. (5) test_emergent_concept_participates_in_assignment — after crystallization, new observation matches emergent concept. (6) test_split_recommendation_fires — concept with 10 diverse members has variance > SPLIT_THRESHOLD. (7) test_merge_recommendation_fires — two concepts with near-identical centroids flagged. E2E (scripts/e2e_concept_lifecycle.sh — NEW SCRIPT): (8) Fresh init → observe 5 related findings → braid status shows concept with member_count=5 (not 0). (9) Observe 10 diverse findings → braid harvest → '2 new concepts crystallized'. (10) After harvest, new observation matches emergent concept (visible in observe response). (11) braid status shows accurate member counts for all concepts. (12) braid status shows split/merge recommendations where appropriate. (13) Full lifecycle: init → 15 observations → harvest → 5 more observations → verify emergent concepts get new members → status shows evolving concept inventory. PROPTEST: (14) For any sequence of N observations (5..30), after lifecycle-observe wiring: sum of all concept member_counts = number of categorized observations. (15) For any concept, total_weight >= member_count (minimum weight per member is 1.0). FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Each test logs concept names, member counts, centroid norms, variance values, and cosine similarities between centroid and members. E2E script logs every braid observe response and every braid status output with timestamps. DEPENDS-ON: LIFECYCLE-OBSERVE, LIFECYCLE-HARVEST, LIFECYCLE-STATUS. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (test module), crates/braid/src/commands/ (integration tests), scripts/e2e_concept_lifecycle.sh (new)" :op :assert}
